The 50 young mechanics receiving training on Automobile and Mechatronics in Kaduna under the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) in Yobe State will be empowered with start-up tools after completion, the coordinator of the programme, Musa Sale Damagum has said. SDGs in Yobe had earlier this year, sponsored 50 young mechanics for three months training and skills upgrade at Kakuri PAN Learning Centre of Peugeot Automobile Nigeria Kaduna. Damagum said that the SDGs is also engaging Bank of Industries among other relevant organisations on how to set up the trained technicians under one modern workshop (Modular Workshop) where all technicians of whatever specialisation will work under one roof at a time. The coordinator disclosed that “There are two options after the training. One is for them to go back to their workshops and impact what they learn to younger ones and the other is to see if we can set them into working groups where we can have all of them, mechanics, air conditions technicians, general engine repair, car wash among others under one modular workshop.” He said 6 modular workshops are billed for construction in Potiskum, Damaturu, Gashu’a, Nguru, Geidam and Buni-Yadi while well-to-do in the society will also be encouraged to key into constructing such workshop across the state. “The objective of the training was to upgrade the skills of our mechanics because we noticed that most of them are lagging behind as they probably learn the job from cars manufactured in 60s, 70, and 80s and new generation cars are ICT driven. “With the training, we expect that their productivity as well as marketability will improve and it is also good for car owners including government agencies and organisations who constantly buy cars and in a year or two they got damaged due to poor maintenance knowledge by our mechanics,” Damagum added. The coordinator said if not because of the COVID-19 pandemic the trainees could have graduated by now thereby adding impetus to the ongoing efforts of reducing unemployment among the youths by Buni administration as there will be transfer of knowledge.